deteriorate /dɪˈtɪərɪəˌreɪt/

(deteriorating,deteriorated,deteriorates) 

1. V-I If something deteriorates , it becomes worse in some way. 恶化 

例： There are fears that the situation might deteriorate into full-scale war. 人们担心局势会恶化为全面战争。 

2. deterioration N-UNCOUNT 恶化 

例： ...concern about the rapid deterioration in relations between the two countries. …对两国关系迅速恶化的担忧。

